<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Stands appear associated with past burns that occur in the late summer or fall. The stands occupy areas where fire frequencies are moderate to relatively high, such as in the borderland between desert and chaparral types. Individuals of <i>Achnatherum speciosum </i>survive fires, sprout rapidly, set seed, and colonize burned areas more rapidly than the formerly dominant shrubs (Humphrey 1974). However, the presence of <i>Bromus rubens, Schismus </i>spp., and other non-natives increases fire frequencies, and the invasive qualities of these species impose a decline on the importance of this bunchgrass.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
